item.title: OnShape & MKCad
item.description: If you are an OnShape user and an FRC team, you’ve probably heard of MKCad, which is a user created FRC parts library by the Team 1836: The Milkenknights. Here are some tricks to help folks make the most out of MKCad: Easy way to find Official MKCad documents Using the newly created MKCAD label Inserting from MKCad without reassembling One common annoyance is when adding parts from MKCAD avoid all the copies.
